1
00:00:01,891 --> 00:00:05,058
(gentle techno music)

2
00:00:12,984 --> 00:00:16,484
(gentle orchestral music)

3
00:02:01,673 --> 00:02:04,586
(dog barking)

4
00:02:04,586 --> 00:02:06,850
- [Natalie] Sandy, bring in the presents.

5
00:02:06,850 --> 00:02:07,713
- Okay, Mom.

6
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:14,524
That looks great, Mom.

7
00:02:14,524 --> 00:02:16,550
Did you get the candles?

8
00:02:16,550 --> 00:02:18,420
- 22 and one to grow on.

9
00:02:19,330 --> 00:02:22,243
I can't wait for Matt to get here.

10
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:27,560
Why aren't you dressed yet?

11
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,720
- I'm gonna take a walk.

12
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:30,567
- Didn't you just do the treadmill?

13
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:32,380
- The doctor told me to exercise.

14
00:02:32,380 --> 00:02:34,028
- [Natalie] He also told
you not to overdo it.

15
00:02:34,028 --> 00:02:35,190
- Yeah, I know.

16
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:37,700
You're putting them too far apart.

17
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:40,527
She won't be able to blow them out.

18
00:02:44,129 --> 00:02:44,962
- He means well.

19
00:02:44,962 --> 00:02:45,990
- I'm moving out.

20
00:02:45,990 --> 00:02:46,907
- Now, stop that.

21
00:02:46,907 --> 00:02:48,751
- Ah, come on, Mom,
this just isn't working.

22
00:02:48,751 --> 00:02:50,980
- You're dad wants you here and so do I.

23
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:54,556
- I'll have enough money as
soon as the divorce is final.

24
00:02:54,556 --> 00:02:58,056
(gentle orchestral music)

25
00:03:08,408 --> 00:03:11,075
(country music)

26
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,580
- Ms. Pierce is here.

27
00:03:22,580 --> 00:03:24,623
- Oh, I forgot all about her.

28
00:03:27,405 --> 00:03:28,320
Can you take her please?

29
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,153
- I already offered.

30
00:03:29,153 --> 00:03:30,050
She said you're the only one here

31
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:31,798
who can cover her bald spot.

32
00:03:31,798 --> 00:03:32,760
- Oh, I'm gonna be late again.

33
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:33,930
My dad's gonna kill me.

34
00:03:33,930 --> 00:03:35,150
- Come on, Sarah, you
can have her in and out

35
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:36,040
in no time.

36
00:03:44,086 --> 00:03:47,003
- [Sandy] Ooh, look, here they are.

37
00:03:49,607 --> 00:03:50,440
- Hi.

38
00:03:52,993 --> 00:03:54,558
Angel boy.

39
00:03:54,558 --> 00:03:56,254
- [Martha] Hi, Mom.

40
00:03:56,254 --> 00:03:57,461
- Hi, Roger.
- Hi.

41
00:03:57,461 --> 00:03:59,110
- [Natalie] Give Grandma a kiss.

42
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:00,430
- I hope we're not late.

43
00:04:00,430 --> 00:04:01,890
- You are not late.

44
00:04:01,890 --> 00:04:03,683
You're right on the dot.

45
00:04:03,683 --> 00:04:04,983
Thank you.

46
00:04:04,983 --> 00:04:06,240
- Where's the birthday girl?

47
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:08,630
- You know, Sarah, she
lives in her own time zone.

48
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:10,630
- Uh-huh, don't start.

49
00:04:10,630 --> 00:04:12,213
She'll be here any minute.

50
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,807
- I'm gonna go watch the
end of the game, okay?

51
00:04:15,807 --> 00:04:17,240
- Okay.

52
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:19,423
- Let's take this off, it's hot.

53
00:04:19,423 --> 00:04:20,425
- I will do it.

54
00:04:20,425 --> 00:04:22,360
- You'll do it? Okay.

55
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,460
How was your last day?

56
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:24,952
- Actually, it was really nice.

57
00:04:24,952 --> 00:04:27,213
They offered to double
my salary if I'd stay

58
00:04:27,213 --> 00:04:28,340
and my new boss called.

59
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:30,620
I'm getting a company car.

60
00:04:30,620 --> 00:04:31,914
- Terrific.
- Yeah.

61
00:04:31,914 --> 00:04:33,328
- Easy, easy.

62
00:04:33,328 --> 00:04:35,568
- There he is. Hey.

63
00:04:35,568 --> 00:04:37,420
How you doing?

64
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:39,023
- Fine, fine.

65
00:04:40,430 --> 00:04:41,670
- Matty.

66
00:04:41,670 --> 00:04:42,800
- Guess what?

67
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,340
I'm getting a company car

68
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:46,415
and a corner office, what
do you think of that?

69
00:04:46,415 --> 00:04:47,494
- What do I think? Well,
I think it's great.

70
00:04:47,494 --> 00:04:48,630
You know what I think.

71
00:04:48,630 --> 00:04:49,840
- No, I don't.

72
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,610
You never said a word about my new job.

73
00:04:51,610 --> 00:04:53,500
- [John] Oh, honey, come on.

74
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:56,370
- Grandma has a surprise
for you in the kitchen

75
00:04:56,370 --> 00:04:58,420
and Grandma needs you to carve the roast.

76
00:05:01,444 --> 00:05:04,361
(traffic whirring)

77
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:12,560
- Amy, don't run off like that.

78
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:13,393
Give me your hand, come on.

79
00:05:13,393 --> 00:05:14,732
We gotta get home.

80
00:05:14,732 --> 00:05:16,700
We're having a very
special dinner tonight.

81
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:17,569
- How come?

82
00:05:17,569 --> 00:05:18,910
- To celebrate Aunt Lydia's new job.

83
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:21,025
- Are we having hot dogs?

84
00:05:21,025 --> 00:05:22,581
- No.

85
00:05:22,581 --> 00:05:23,840
That's your favorite meal.

86
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:26,133
Aunt Lydia likes my stir, remember.

87
00:05:27,254 --> 00:05:28,320
And she also likes ice cream.

88
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:30,060
- With chocolate sauce?

89
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:31,320
- Yeah, tons of it.

90
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,637
Oh, you're okay.

91
00:05:35,298 --> 00:05:38,562
(engine revving)

92
00:05:38,562 --> 00:05:41,145
(Amy laughing)

93
00:05:43,053 --> 00:05:43,886
What's the matter?

94
00:05:43,886 --> 00:05:45,886
- Somebody's calling me.

95
00:05:46,788 --> 00:05:47,991
- That's just the wind.

96
00:05:47,991 --> 00:05:48,888
- [Danny] Amy.

97
00:05:48,888 --> 00:05:50,349
- It makes funny noises sometimes.

98
00:05:50,349 --> 00:05:52,682
- No, I heard a man, listen.

99
00:05:57,512 --> 00:05:58,512
- God, jeez.

100
00:06:01,503 --> 00:06:03,747
You are a crazy fool.

101
00:06:03,747 --> 00:06:06,663
- Did I scare you? I didn't mean to.

102
00:06:06,663 --> 00:06:08,135
Hey, Danielle, do you think you could talk

103
00:06:08,135 --> 00:06:10,230
to your sister for me?

104
00:06:10,230 --> 00:06:13,300
See if I can, she won't
have nothing to do with me.

105
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:15,467
- You're such a loser, Danny.

106
00:06:15,467 --> 00:06:16,770
Lydia finally figured it out.

107
00:06:16,770 --> 00:06:19,070
She wants you to stay away.

108
00:06:19,070 --> 00:06:19,903
So do I.

109
00:06:21,856 --> 00:06:22,993
- Bye, Amy.

110
00:06:27,622 --> 00:06:30,372
(women laughing)

111
00:06:31,527 --> 00:06:33,415
- [Sarah] Oh, my God, you guys.

112
00:06:33,415 --> 00:06:34,780
Thank you so much.

113
00:06:34,780 --> 00:06:35,613
You put a lot of thought into this.

114
00:06:35,613 --> 00:06:36,950
- Happy birthday.
- Don't lose it.

115
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:39,617
- Hey, everybody look over here.

116
00:06:40,930 --> 00:06:41,763
Perfect.

117
00:06:41,763 --> 00:06:42,860
- [John] Thank you for coming.

118
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:45,680
- Martha, do you have a sitter for Sunday?

119
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,664
- Yep, I'm all set.

120
00:06:46,664 --> 00:06:48,300
Is Ed watching the motel?

121
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,033
- No, he had to go to a funeral.

122
00:06:51,070 --> 00:06:51,970
- I'm gonna do it.

123
00:06:55,010 --> 00:06:55,860
Oh, give me a break, Martha.

124
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:57,760
I think I can handle it for one night.

125
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:03,674
- Mom, come on.

126
00:07:03,674 --> 00:07:05,000
Man of the Year is a big honor.

127
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,970
It's an important night for Dad.

128
00:07:05,970 --> 00:07:07,645
You can't count on Sarah.

129
00:07:07,645 --> 00:07:10,060
- You are something.

130
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:11,774
Sarah wants to go to Dad's party,

131
00:07:11,774 --> 00:07:13,480
but she knows we're in a bind,

132
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,760
so she offered to watch the motel.

133
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:16,530
She's trying to be more responsible.

134
00:07:16,530 --> 00:07:18,820
- She was late for her own birthday party.

135
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:19,750
- She had to work.

136
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,191
- Why are you always defending her?

137
00:07:21,191 --> 00:07:22,973
- Why are you always attacking her?

138
00:07:23,864 --> 00:07:24,697
(Martha scoffs)

139
00:07:24,697 --> 00:07:27,549
- Come on, Martha, let's go.
- Goodnight.

140
00:07:27,549 --> 00:07:28,549
- Goodnight.

141
00:07:30,941 --> 00:07:33,884
Call me when you get home.

142
00:07:33,884 --> 00:07:36,765
(engine revving)

143
00:07:36,765 --> 00:07:40,265
(gentle orchestral music)

144
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:47,457
- It was very pretty.

145
00:07:47,457 --> 00:07:48,882
Why don't you go get
that little candlestick

146
00:07:48,882 --> 00:07:50,153
off my bureau.

147
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:54,941
- Hi, Amy.
- Hey.

148
00:07:54,941 --> 00:07:55,774
- Hi.

149
00:07:57,220 --> 00:07:58,053
I quit.

150
00:07:59,739 --> 00:08:01,083
- [Danielle] What do you mean you quit?

151
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,370
- I mean my boss is kind of a jerk.

152
00:08:04,370 --> 00:08:05,900
He like made me work on my lunch hour

153
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,500
and everything, so, I quit.

154
00:08:09,881 --> 00:08:13,293
- You couldn't just last through one day?

155
00:08:14,710 --> 00:08:17,614
- Danielle, please, don't get
all peeved out, all right?

156
00:08:17,614 --> 00:08:19,080
- It's not that big a deal.

157
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:20,800
I just quit.

158
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,863
- It was a good job, Lydia.

159
00:08:24,210 --> 00:08:26,988
- Yeah, well, not as good as my new one.

160
00:08:26,988 --> 00:08:28,523
- What are you talking about?

161
00:08:29,540 --> 00:08:30,940
- Well, today on my way home,

162
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:32,440
I was walking by that
new market, you know,

163
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:34,625
and they're like looking for cashiers,

164
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:36,470
so I met up with the manager

165
00:08:36,470 --> 00:08:39,293
and he thinks I got a pretty good chance.

166
00:08:40,890 --> 00:08:42,730
- Honey, you can't just go jumping around

167
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:43,563
from job to job.

168
00:08:43,563 --> 00:08:44,790
- I know, this job pays
like 12 bucks an hour.

169
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:46,573
Is that all right?

170
00:08:46,573 --> 00:08:48,203
Amy, how are you?

171
00:08:50,410 --> 00:08:53,430
- We've got ice cream
with chocolate sauce.

172
00:08:53,430 --> 00:08:54,263
- We do?

173
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:57,633
- Honey, why don't you go wash your hands.

174
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:06,073
I saw Danny today.

175
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:09,183
He followed me and Amy.

176
00:09:10,082 --> 00:09:11,230
He nearly scared us to death.

177
00:09:11,230 --> 00:09:15,930
- Yeah, did he say
something or what'd he say?

178
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,243
- He wants you back.

179
00:09:19,180 --> 00:09:21,000
- Ain't happening this time.

180
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:21,833
It's not.

181
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:26,943
I mean, I'm not scared
of him anymore, you know.

182
00:09:26,943 --> 00:09:29,443
(man banging)

183
00:09:31,435 --> 00:09:33,484
- [Man] Anyone in there?

184
00:09:33,484 --> 00:09:34,871
Fire, wake up.

185
00:09:34,871 --> 00:09:35,722
- Danielle!

186
00:09:35,722 --> 00:09:36,555
Danielle!

187
00:09:36,555 --> 00:09:38,222
Amy, there's a fire.

188
00:09:39,727 --> 00:09:42,477
(sirens blaring)

189
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:55,257
- [Amy] The windows,
let's get to the window.

190
00:09:55,257 --> 00:09:58,007
(dramatic music)

191
00:10:07,019 --> 00:10:09,519
(baby crying)

192
00:10:10,368 --> 00:10:13,035
(siren blaring)

193
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:17,330
- Said it was the wiring.

194
00:10:17,330 --> 00:10:19,633
It's been shorting out for months.

195
00:10:20,565 --> 00:10:23,315
(dramatic music)

196
00:10:37,216 --> 00:10:41,099
- [Child] Here, kitty,
come on, kitty, kitty.

197
00:10:41,099 --> 00:10:44,099
(suspenseful music)

198
00:10:57,141 --> 00:11:00,641
(gentle orchestral music)

199
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,583
(bell ringing)

200
00:11:28,949 --> 00:11:29,899
- Hi.
- Good evening.

201
00:11:29,899 --> 00:11:32,030
- I'm really sorry to get you out of bed.

202
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:33,632
We just had a fire in our building

203
00:11:33,632 --> 00:11:35,445
and the fireman said you might put us up

204
00:11:35,445 --> 00:11:37,750
for the night?

205
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:40,593
He says that you
sometimes help people out.

206
00:11:42,464 --> 00:11:43,620
I'll be honest with you.

207
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:45,370
I don't have any money right now,

208
00:11:45,370 --> 00:11:46,910
but I'll pay you back.

209
00:11:46,910 --> 00:11:48,550
I promise.

210
00:11:48,550 --> 00:11:50,112
- I've got money, Mommy.

211
00:11:50,112 --> 00:11:54,612
I can pay.

212
00:11:54,612 --> 00:11:57,450
- Well, let's not worry about that now.

213
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:58,750
First let's get everyone to bed.

214
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:00,731
- Thank you so much.

215
00:12:00,731 --> 00:12:01,803
I promise I'll pay you back.

216
00:12:01,803 --> 00:12:03,380
- It's all right.

217
00:12:03,380 --> 00:12:04,343
Right this way.

218
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:07,060
Just follow me back here.

219
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:09,765
I've got an extra room for you.

220
00:12:09,765 --> 00:12:12,265
(dog barking)

221
00:12:24,596 --> 00:12:26,002
- Hey, good morning.

222
00:12:26,002 --> 00:12:27,050
- Good morning.

223
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:28,270
- We go there late last night.

224
00:12:28,270 --> 00:12:29,420
And I'm wondering if you could do our room

225
00:12:29,420 --> 00:12:30,520
a little later.

226
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:32,600
My little girl and my
sister are still asleep.

227
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:33,439
- Oh, sure, that's not a problem.

228
00:12:33,439 --> 00:12:34,591
- Thank you very much.

229
00:12:34,591 --> 00:12:36,008
- It's all right.

230
00:12:40,084 --> 00:12:43,084
(suspenseful music)

231
00:12:45,821 --> 00:12:48,691
- Now's the chance, buddy.

232
00:12:48,691 --> 00:12:51,813
- Nah, not now, she's
got the kid with her.

233
00:12:53,605 --> 00:12:56,025
I want her later, alone.

234
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:58,691
- I ain't got nothing but time.

235
00:12:58,691 --> 00:13:01,441
(engine revving)

236
00:13:20,217 --> 00:13:22,967
(Sarah knocking)

237
00:13:24,210 --> 00:13:25,050
- Hi.
- Hi.

238
00:13:25,050 --> 00:13:26,243
- My mom keeps these around for my nephew.

239
00:13:26,243 --> 00:13:28,600
I thought maybe the little
girl would like them.

240
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,263
- Oh, cool, thanks, come on in.

241
00:13:36,225 --> 00:13:37,490
(door closes)

242
00:13:37,490 --> 00:13:38,330
- [Lydia] So you cut hair.

243
00:13:38,330 --> 00:13:39,823
That's like a tough job.

244
00:13:42,140 --> 00:13:44,190
Do you live here like all the time.

245
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:45,023
- I'm trying to save up money.

246
00:13:45,023 --> 00:13:48,277
I got into some trouble with credit cards.

247
00:13:48,277 --> 00:13:49,577
- Oh, maxed them out, huh?

248
00:13:50,496 --> 00:13:52,113
- Good thing for my dad.

249
00:13:53,030 --> 00:13:55,480
- [Lydia] He seems real
nice, real considerate.

250
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:56,380
- Yeah, he is.

251
00:13:56,380 --> 00:13:58,192
He's always doing things for other people,

252
00:13:58,192 --> 00:14:02,140
always helping out, even now.

253
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:02,973
- [Lydia] What do you mean?

254
00:14:02,973 --> 00:14:04,730
- I mean he had a heart attack.

255
00:14:04,730 --> 00:14:05,563
- Wow, sorry.

256
00:14:05,563 --> 00:14:07,840
I mean, you'd never know
it if you looked at him.

257
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:09,890
- Yeah, it runs in his family.

258
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:13,063
His dad died really young.

259
00:14:15,033 --> 00:14:17,963
I think he's afraid the same
thing's gonna happen to him.

260
00:14:27,754 --> 00:14:28,587
- Dad.

261
00:14:30,690 --> 00:14:32,110
I just, um, I wanted to thank you

262
00:14:32,110 --> 00:14:33,360
for bailing me out again.

263
00:14:35,490 --> 00:14:36,740
- You missed a spot here.

264
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:39,680
- You know, I learned my lesson this time.

265
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:41,633
I did, I'm not gonna screw up again.

266
00:14:44,042 --> 00:14:44,875
I promise.

267
00:14:46,517 --> 00:14:48,184
- Good. That's good.

268
00:14:49,450 --> 00:14:50,442
- Dad, I'm gonna be done here in a second.

269
00:14:50,442 --> 00:14:53,061
Do you want to play cards or something?

270
00:14:53,061 --> 00:14:55,000
