00:27:48,859 --> 00:27:50,747
All right, let's go.

544
00:27:50,747 --> 00:27:53,330
(gentle music)

545
00:28:00,027 --> 00:28:01,212
Do it.

546
00:28:01,212 --> 00:28:03,795
(gentle music)

547
00:28:11,963 --> 00:28:14,796
(thunder roaring)

548
00:28:17,126 --> 00:28:19,499
(dog barking)

549
00:28:19,499 --> 00:28:20,332
Let's go.

550
00:28:50,294 --> 00:28:53,024
- What the hell is going on?

551
00:28:53,024 --> 00:28:54,222
What the hell is going on, where is she?

552
00:28:54,222 --> 00:28:55,271
- Take these.

553
00:28:55,271 --> 00:28:56,279
- Where's Sarah?

554
00:28:56,279 --> 00:28:57,112
- She's gonna be all right.

555
00:28:57,112 --> 00:28:58,032
- Danny.
- Take that.

556
00:28:58,032 --> 00:28:59,696
- Danny, I swear to God.

557
00:28:59,696 --> 00:29:01,964
- Would you just...

558
00:29:01,964 --> 00:29:03,231
- Rob, get off me.

559
00:29:03,231 --> 00:29:04,291
Where is she?

560
00:29:04,291 --> 00:29:05,294
- Get in the car.

561
00:29:05,294 --> 00:29:06,550
- [Lydia] What the hell did you do?

562
00:29:06,550 --> 00:29:08,788
- [Rob] Just shut up, everything's cool.

563
00:29:08,788 --> 00:29:10,358
(engine revving)

564
00:29:10,358 --> 00:29:11,883
We gotta make it up there.

565
00:29:11,883 --> 00:29:13,887
- [Lydia] Where is she, Danny?

566
00:29:13,887 --> 00:29:17,031
- Stop asking questions, all right?

567
00:29:17,031 --> 00:29:19,864
(tires squealing)

568
00:29:29,060 --> 00:29:30,408
- Is there anybody else
that we can talk to?

569
00:29:30,408 --> 00:29:32,623
Anybody else from the beauty parlor?

570
00:29:33,580 --> 00:29:35,190
Okay, thank you.

571
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:37,190
Please let us know if you hear from her.

572
00:29:38,355 --> 00:29:40,250
- Don't you think we
should call the police?

573
00:29:40,250 --> 00:29:42,153
- No, Mom, you're getting
yourself all upset over nothing.

574
00:29:42,153 --> 00:29:44,970
- Your sister's been
missing for five hours.

575
00:29:44,970 --> 00:29:46,353
- Mom, she's fine.

576
00:29:47,293 --> 00:29:49,336
Look, call us when you hear from her.

577
00:29:49,336 --> 00:29:51,186
We have to go relieve the babysitter.

578
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:54,390
- Goodnight, Daddy.

579
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:57,770
- It's gonna be fine.

580
00:30:00,390 --> 00:30:01,843
- [Roger] It's gonna be okay, Mom.

581
00:30:03,550 --> 00:30:07,016
- Maybe I, maybe I should drive around,

582
00:30:07,016 --> 00:30:08,663
see if I can spot her car.

583
00:30:11,890 --> 00:30:12,840
- I'll go with you.

584
00:30:14,024 --> 00:30:15,024
- All right.

585
00:30:21,768 --> 00:30:24,268
(door closes)

586
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:27,420
- God, the stunts Sarah pulls.

587
00:30:27,420 --> 00:30:28,480
I can't believe I have to start

588
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:29,630
a new job tomorrow and now all I can do

589
00:30:29,630 --> 00:30:31,240
is think about her.

590
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:32,073
She's fine, right?

591
00:30:32,073 --> 00:30:33,993
- Yeah, yeah, she's gonna be fine.

592
00:30:35,112 --> 00:30:37,695
(gentle music)

593
00:30:47,382 --> 00:30:48,215
- Nothing.

594
00:30:53,872 --> 00:30:55,705
- I called the police.

595
00:30:57,233 --> 00:30:59,300
- Why? Why would you do that?

596
00:30:59,300 --> 00:31:01,910
- They won't officially
list her as missing

597
00:31:01,910 --> 00:31:03,723
until she's gone for 24 hours.

598
00:31:04,870 --> 00:31:06,570
I did talk to Ben Warren.

599
00:31:06,570 --> 00:31:08,070
I gave him a description of the car

600
00:31:08,070 --> 00:31:10,710
and I told him what Sarah was wearing

601
00:31:11,696 --> 00:31:14,721
and he said he would do everything he can.

602
00:31:14,721 --> 00:31:17,304
(gentle music)

603
00:31:25,345 --> 00:31:27,947
(thunder rolling)

604
00:31:27,947 --> 00:31:30,697
(dramatic music)

605
00:31:42,004 --> 00:31:44,671
(siren blaring)

606
00:31:49,309 --> 00:31:53,181
- Be cool, just be cool.

607
00:31:53,181 --> 00:31:54,220
Evening, Officer.

608
00:31:54,220 --> 00:31:56,993
- There's an attempt
to locate on this car.

609
00:31:57,959 --> 00:31:59,805
Is there a Sarah Porter in this vehicle.

610
00:31:59,805 --> 00:32:02,013
- Yeah, I'm Sarah
Porter, I'm Sarah Porter.

611
00:32:02,013 --> 00:32:04,122
- Says here you're wearing a red sweater

612
00:32:04,122 --> 00:32:05,289
and tan pants.

613
00:32:07,570 --> 00:32:10,570
- You know what, I just changed, so.

614
00:32:11,517 --> 00:32:13,959
- Also a ring, heart shaped.

615
00:32:13,959 --> 00:32:15,459
- Yeah, see, ring.

616
00:32:20,615 --> 00:32:21,776
- Okay.

617
00:32:21,776 --> 00:32:22,609
- Okay.

618
00:32:22,609 --> 00:32:25,320
- Make sure to call your mom.

619
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:26,153
Drive safe.

620
00:32:26,153 --> 00:32:27,426
- [Lydia] Thanks.

621
00:32:34,776 --> 00:32:36,024
(phone ringing)

622
00:32:36,024 --> 00:32:37,191
- I'll get it.

623
00:32:39,992 --> 00:32:40,825
Yes?

624
00:32:45,140 --> 00:32:45,973
Thank God.

625
00:32:48,430 --> 00:32:49,263
Thank you.

626
00:32:51,395 --> 00:32:53,130
- [Sandy] What is she doing driving around

627
00:32:53,130 --> 00:32:55,170
with two guys, who are they?

628
00:32:55,170 --> 00:32:56,003
- I don't know.

629
00:32:56,003 --> 00:32:58,560
Maybe they're friends,
maybe it's a boyfriend.

630
00:32:58,560 --> 00:32:59,859
- Mom, Sarah doesn't have a boyfriend.

631
00:32:59,859 --> 00:33:02,453
- Maybe she does, maybe
she just didn't tell us.

632
00:33:03,570 --> 00:33:04,788
- What are they doing
in the middle of nowhere

633
00:33:04,788 --> 00:33:06,390
at 2 o'clock in the morning

634
00:33:06,390 --> 00:33:08,510
and why hasn't she called us?

635
00:33:08,510 --> 00:33:10,450
She obviously knows we're looking for her.

636
00:33:10,450 --> 00:33:11,640
The cops must have told her that

637
00:33:11,640 --> 00:33:13,408
and besides didn't the cop say

638
00:33:13,408 --> 00:33:15,990
that one of the guys was driving.

639
00:33:15,990 --> 00:33:18,130
Sarah never lets anyone
behind the wheel of that car.

640
00:33:18,130 --> 00:33:19,800
She loves that car.

641
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:21,900
Mom, this just doesn't make any sense.

642
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:23,410
- What are you saying?

643
00:33:23,410 --> 00:33:24,790
That wasn't your sister in the car?

644
00:33:24,790 --> 00:33:26,787
- [Sandy] I don't know what I'm saying.

645
00:33:26,787 --> 00:33:28,863
I'm just thinking out loud.

646
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:32,050
Dad, what should we do?

647
00:33:34,980 --> 00:33:36,353
- It's the middle of the night.

648
00:33:38,060 --> 00:33:39,860
There's nothing we can do right now.

649
00:33:43,730 --> 00:33:46,700
(clock ticking)

650
00:33:46,700 --> 00:33:49,200
(dog barking)

651
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:02,274
- I'm waiting for Ben
to get to the station.

652
00:34:02,274 --> 00:34:03,840
Then Sandy and I are gonna go see him.

653
00:34:03,840 --> 00:34:04,763
He'll help us.

654
00:34:05,824 --> 00:34:09,003
- Honey, we're not even
sure that we need help.

655
00:34:10,160 --> 00:34:11,360
- Fine, John.

656
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:13,010
You say here.

657
00:34:13,010 --> 00:34:14,410
Just ignore what's going on.

658
00:34:15,446 --> 00:34:16,896
We both know how you do that.

659
00:34:20,374 --> 00:34:21,207
I'm sorry.

660
00:34:23,590 --> 00:34:24,740
She's in trouble, John.

661
00:34:29,380 --> 00:34:31,947
- Natalie, I think you're
overreacting to this.

662
00:34:31,947 --> 00:34:33,700
I think you just gotta give her...

663
00:34:33,700 --> 00:34:36,553
- You remember when she was
little in the second grade.

664
00:34:37,570 --> 00:34:39,783
I was out shopping and I had

665
00:34:39,783 --> 00:34:43,160
this terrible feeling
something had happened to her.

666
00:34:43,160 --> 00:34:45,100
I had to get to that school.

667
00:34:45,100 --> 00:34:45,960
Do you remember?

668
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:48,183
She fell off the jungle
gym and broke her arm.

669
00:34:49,020 --> 00:34:50,570
They'd been trying to reach me.

670
00:34:52,060 --> 00:34:54,710
I had a sixth sense about
Sarah, John, you know that.

671
00:34:57,997 --> 00:35:00,733
I have to go to the police.

672
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:04,203
Sarah wasn't in that car, I know it.

673
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:09,387
Sandy are you ready?

674
00:35:09,387 --> 00:35:12,288
- [Sandy] Come on, Mom, let's go.

675
00:35:12,288 --> 00:35:14,871
(gentle music)

676
00:35:38,422 --> 00:35:41,089
(phone ringing)

677
00:35:48,022 --> 00:35:48,855
- Hello?

678
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:51,833
Yeah, yeah.

679
00:35:53,910 --> 00:35:55,773
Yes, that's my daughter's car.

680
00:35:58,411 --> 00:36:00,270
Yeah, just a second, let me get something

681
00:36:00,270 --> 00:36:01,653
to write oh, hold on.

682
00:36:04,095 --> 00:36:05,845
Yeah, okay, go ahead.

683
00:36:07,284 --> 00:36:08,117
Yeah.

684
00:36:10,474 --> 00:36:11,307
Right.

685
00:36:14,670 --> 00:36:15,670
Thank you very much.

686
00:36:22,606 --> 00:36:25,189
(John sighing)

687
00:36:27,638 --> 00:36:29,430
- They found the car in the
worst section of Rockwater.

688
00:36:29,430 --> 00:36:31,430
You're damn lucky there's anything left.

689
00:36:34,070 --> 00:36:36,040
Somebody parked it right
next to a fire hydrant.

690
00:36:36,040 --> 00:36:36,873
Not too bright.

691
00:36:40,340 --> 00:36:41,630
There's a $90 impound fee

692
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:42,630
and then it's yours.

693
00:36:48,398 --> 00:36:51,148
(engine revving)

694
00:36:52,494 --> 00:36:55,077
(gentle music)

695
00:37:21,788 --> 00:37:22,855
- Are you sure he knows we're here.

696
00:37:22,855 --> 00:37:23,950
- [Woman] Yes, ma'am.

697
00:37:23,950 --> 00:37:25,436
- Mom, maybe we should
come back another time.

698
00:37:25,436 --> 00:37:26,500
They seem pretty busy.

699
00:37:26,500 --> 00:37:28,400
- [Ben] Okay, Walt, I'll let you know.

700
00:37:30,210 --> 00:37:31,480
- Hello, Natalie.
- Ben.

701
00:37:31,480 --> 00:37:32,423
- Thank you for seeing us.

702
00:37:32,423 --> 00:37:34,080
You remember my daughter, Sandy.

703
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:35,580
- Of course, Sandy, nice to see you again.

704
00:37:35,580 --> 00:37:37,100
Natalie, as soon as I got your phone call,

705
00:37:37,100 --> 00:37:39,010
I got a report from the
North Adams precinct

706
00:37:39,010 --> 00:37:40,260
from an officer, George Colby.

707
00:37:40,260 --> 00:37:41,733
Now he's the officer that
pulled Sarah's car over

708
00:37:41,733 --> 00:37:43,930
and everything seemed to be in order

709
00:37:43,930 --> 00:37:46,130
so I'm not sure I see
what the problem is here.

710
00:37:46,130 --> 00:37:47,790
- We don't think that
was Sarah in the car.

711
00:37:47,790 --> 00:37:49,242
She would have called home.

712
00:37:49,242 --> 00:37:51,520
It doesn't make sense
she'd be 50 miles from home

713
00:37:51,520 --> 00:37:52,815
in the middle of the night.

714
00:37:52,815 --> 00:37:55,097
- Why don't we go inside?

715
00:37:55,097 --> 00:37:57,220
- Here's the file you asked for Ben.

716
00:37:57,220 --> 00:37:58,223
- Thank you.

717
00:37:58,223 --> 00:37:59,530
You know, Natalie, you're a good mom

718
00:37:59,530 --> 00:38:01,070
and good moms have a tendency to worry

719
00:38:01,070 --> 00:38:02,410
about their daughters even if

720
00:38:02,410 --> 00:38:05,400
they're just late from
the mall by half an hour.

721
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:06,960
- She's not late.

722
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:08,230
She's missing.

723
00:38:08,230 --> 00:38:09,359
Over 15 hours.

724
00:38:09,359 --> 00:38:11,258
This is not something Sarah would do.

725
00:38:11,258 --> 00:38:13,540
- No, it's something
she has done, Natalie.

726
00:38:13,540 --> 00:38:14,810
You don't remember that rock concert

727
00:38:14,810 --> 00:38:17,910
about two years ago, what
was she gone two days?

728
00:38:17,910 --> 00:38:19,080
- This is different.

729
00:38:19,080 --> 00:38:20,410
She was just going to the florist.

730
00:38:20,410 --> 00:38:21,381
She was coming right back.

731
00:38:21,381 --> 00:38:22,940
(phone buzzing)

732
00:38:22,940 --> 00:38:23,773
- [Woman] Lieutenant?

733
00:38:23,773 --> 00:38:24,606
- Excuse me.

734
00:38:24,606 --> 00:38:26,200
Yeah, I'll be right there.

735
00:38:26,200 --> 00:38:28,440
All right, look, here's
what I suggest you do.

736
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:30,070
I think you should probably go home

737
00:38:30,070 --> 00:38:31,430
and stay by the phone because I'm sure

738
00:38:31,430 --> 00:38:33,290
she's gonna be calling you.

739
00:38:33,290 --> 00:38:34,123
- [Woman] Ben we need you.

740
00:38:34,123 --> 00:38:36,760
- All right, all right, I'm on my way.

741
00:38:36,760 --> 00:38:38,713
I'm sorry, Natalie, can you excuse me.

742
00:38:43,340 --> 00:38:44,650
- Ben.

743
00:38:44,650 --> 00:38:46,690
Something's happened to her.

744
00:38:46,690 --> 00:38:47,810
I know it.

745
00:38:47,810 --> 00:38:50,110
You have to put out a
missing person's report.

746
00:38:51,050 --> 00:38:53,490
- I can't put out a
missing person's report

747
00:38:53,490 --> 00:38:55,023
because Sarah's not missing.

748
00:38:56,200 --> 00:38:57,033
Sandy.

749
00:39:01,076 --> 00:39:03,743
(phone ringing)

750
00:39:05,513 --> 00:39:07,846
- Come on, Amy, we gotta go.

751
00:39:09,023 --> 00:39:11,048
- I'm saving money to buy a house.

752
00:39:11,048 --> 00:39:12,598
A big one.

753
00:39:12,598 --> 00:39:15,607
- Oh, well, I will contribute

754
00:39:15,607 --> 00:39:18,477
if you promise me you'll
paint my room pink.

755
00:39:20,481 --> 00:39:22,388
Thank you.

756
00:39:22,388 --> 00:39:24,388
Come on, let's go again.

757
00:39:25,392 --> 00:39:28,202
(Lydia laughing)

758
00:39:28,202 --> 00:39:29,226
- Hey, Amy.

759
00:39:29,226 --> 00:39:30,257
- Hey, Danielle.

760
00:39:30,257 --> 00:39:31,593
Can I get a beer?

761
00:39:36,464 --> 00:39:38,655
- I want you to go into your room.

762
00:39:38,655 --> 00:39:39,658
- [Amy] But Mommy.

763
00:39:39,658 --> 00:39:40,922
- Now.
- Excuse me.

764
00:39:40,922 --> 00:39:43,040
- You're excused. I'm tired.

765
00:39:43,040 --> 00:39:44,193
- Hey, Amy.

766
00:39:45,104 --> 00:39:47,687
(all laughing)

767
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:53,550
- Lydia, I want you and your buddies

768
00:39:53,550 --> 00:39:55,830
to get out of my house right now.

769
00:39:55,830 --> 00:39:57,410
- You mean you?

770
00:39:57,410 --> 00:39:59,440
- But this is my apartment, too.

771
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:00,582
- Dammit, get out of my house,

772
00:40:00,582 --> 00:40:02,566
right now Danny, get the
hell out of my apartment.

773
00:40:02,566 --> 00:40:03,547
- Danielle, would you chill, chill.

774
00:40:03,547 --> 00:40:05,590
- Oh, don't touch me.

775
00:40:05,590 --> 00:40:06,423
Shut up.

776
00:40:06,423 --> 00:40:07,730
- Would you stop it.

777
00:40:07,730 --> 00:40:09,677
Don't talk to my husband like that.

778
00:40:10,863 --> 00:40:13,280
- What are you talking about?

779
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:16,393
- Hey.

780
00:40:17,890 --> 00:40:19,290
- Last night we got married.

781
00:40:21,688 --> 00:40:23,408
- That's the truth, sis.

782
00:40:23,408 --> 00:40:25,252
- Watch the stuff.

783
00:40:25,252 --> 00:40:27,664
- Oh, God.

784
00:40:27,664 --> 00:40:29,371
- I'm sorry, Danielle.

785
00:40:29,371 --> 00:40:31,204
God, will you stop it.

786
00:40:38,150 --> 00:40:38,983
- Dad.

787
00:40:38,983 --> 00:40:39,816
- No, this is Ed.

788
00:40:39,816 --> 00:40:41,158
Is that you, Martha?

789
00:40:41,158 --> 00:40:42,854
- Yeah, is Mom or Dad there?

790
00:40:42,854 --> 00:40:45,077
- No, they're both gone.

791
00:40:45,077 --> 00:40:46,130
I'm not sure where.

792
00:40:46,130 --> 00:40:47,728
- Have you heard from Sarah.

793
00:40:47,728 --> 00:40:51,280
- No, no word from Sarah.

794
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:53,680
- Okay, will you tell them
that I called, please?

795
00:40:53,680 --> 00:40:54,567
- I'll tell them.

796
00:40:54,567 --> 00:40:55,400
- Thanks.

797
00:41:03,083 --> 00:41:06,083
(upbeat rock music)

798
00:41:09,199 --> 00:41:11,642
- Yeah, no that's okay, man.

799
00:41:11,642 --> 00:41:13,870
I'm with it all the way, that's rockin'.

800
00:41:13,870 --> 00:41:14,703
Yeah.

801
00:41:15,710 --> 00:41:16,830
Brother, okay.

802
00:41:16,830 --> 00:41:18,570
No, no, no, I'll get back to you.

803
00:41:18,570 --> 00:41:19,993
Just let me know, cool.

804
00:41:21,470 --> 00:41:22,303
- What?

805
00:41:24,152 --> 00:41:25,549
(Lydia laughing)

806
00:41:25,549 --> 00:41:28,910
What are you, what are you doing?

807
00:41:28,910 --> 00:41:30,863
- Honolulu, Thursday.

808
00:41:32,080 --> 00:41:32,913
- What?

809
00:41:35,460 --> 00:41:38,243
- You see, now that we're married,

810
00:41:39,223 --> 00:41:40,973
I know how to take care of my wife.

811
00:41:42,350 --> 00:41:44,850
- Danny, how you gonna get
the money for Honolulu?

